Native-Slang shader source — stage A notes (regular-text family)
================================================================

One Slang source tree, four targets, regression-gated against the composed
GLSL catalog. `zig build gen-shaders` (nix-shell: slangc 2026.5.2 + naga)
regenerates the checked-in artifacts in src/snail/shader/generated/.

Module layout
-------------
  render_abi.slang      shared ABI constants
  color_common.slang    sRGB transfer + premultiply helpers
  coverage_common.slang root-code / band-span / transfer machinery
  text_coverage.slang   text-family glyph coverage evaluator
  vertex.slang          instance-quad vertex body (dilation math)
  text_main.slang       regular-text fragment logic
  families/text.slang   resource bindings + [shader(...)] entry points

Math is ported 1:1 from src/snail/shader/glsl/ (the behavioral spec —
epsilons, literals, and operation order preserved). Structural changes are
plumbing only: textures and the coverage exponent are function parameters
(no cross-module preprocessor state in Slang), texelFetch(tex, ivec3(l, a),
0) becomes tex.Load(int4(l, a, 0)).

Per-target flag sets (source of truth: build/slang_shaders.zig)
---------------------------------------------------------------
Common: -default-image-format-unknown -entry <e> -stage <s>
        -I src/snail/shader/slang

  vulkan  -DSNAIL_TARGET_VULKAN -target spirv -profile spirv_1_3
  wgsl    -DSNAIL_TARGET_WGSL -target wgsl        (direct; validates in naga)
  gl      -DSNAIL_TARGET_GL -target spirv -profile spirv_1_3
          [fragment only: -emit-spirv-via-glsl -warnings-disable 41012]
          then: naga --input-kind spv --keep-coordinate-space
                --profile core330 | es300

Matrix convention (re-verified empirically for NATIVE Slang)
------------------------------------------------------------
The GLSL-ingestion finding (-matrix-layout-row-major mandatory) does NOT
carry over. For native Slang the DEFAULT layout is correct: `mul(mvp, v)`
emits `RowMajor` + MatrixStride 16 + `OpVectorTimesMatrix(v, M)`, which
reads the CPU's column-major GLSL bytes with GLSL `M * v` semantics
(Vulkan gate: AE = 0 vs the glslc-era baseline). Passing
-matrix-layout-column-major transposes every matrix (blank render). Also
remember the indexing transpose when porting: GLSL `M[c][r]` vs Slang
`M[r][c]` — GLSL's row-gather `vec4(M[0].x, M[1].x, M[2].x, M[3].x)` is
just `mvp[0]` in Slang.

Semantic traps found (stage B must respect all of these)
--------------------------------------------------------
1. SV_VertexID is D3D-semantics: Slang lowers it to VertexIndex−BaseVertex,
   dragging in the DrawParameters capability (a Vulkan device feature the
   demo devices don't enable) and gl_BaseVertex (GL 4.6-only) through naga.
   For SPIR-V targets load the raw builtin via spirv_asm (see
   families/text.slang); WGSL's vertex_index is already raw — keep
   SV_VertexID there.
2. slang direct-SPIR-V loops are the recorded naga-structurizer trap: naga
   buries the loop-exit break inside a do{}while(false) wrapper → the loop
   never terminates → GPU hang / white frame. Any stage with a loop that
   goes through naga must compile -emit-spirv-via-glsl. spirv_asm does not
   compile through the via-glsl backend, so a stage cannot have both a
   loop and spirv_asm. (Text: vertex = spirv_asm + no loops → direct;
   fragment = loops + no spirv_asm → via-glsl.)
3. WGSL clip space is y-up; every other target of ours is Vulkan y-down
   convention. slangc's WGSL backend performs no coordinate-space
   conversion and -fvk-invert-y is a no-op for -target wgsl: negate
   position.y in the WGSL entry (families/text.slang). For the naga GL leg
   the opposite holds: pass --keep-coordinate-space or naga *inserts* a
   flip + depth remap.
4. Texture element types: without -default-image-format-unknown slangc
   guesses an image format (e.g. Rg32ui for Texture2DArray<uint2>) and
   pulls in the StorageImageExtendedFormats capability for load-only
   textures.
5. Descriptor compatibility: declaring bare Texture2DArray (no sampler)
   yields SAMPLED_IMAGE variables, which Vulkan happily binds from the
   existing COMBINED_IMAGE_SAMPLER set — no descriptor-layout change
   needed. WGSL likewise needs no sampler bindings for Load-only use.
6. Entry-point names: single-entry SPIR-V compiles are renamed to `main`;
   -target wgsl keeps the Slang function names (vertexMain/fragmentMain) —
   pipelines must pass them explicitly (see minimal_wgpu createPipelineEntries).
7. Uniform-block names in the naga GL output are generated (and differ per
   SPIR-V leg): SnailPushConstants_std140_block_0Vertex vs
   block_SnailPushConstants_0_block_0Fragment; samplers are
   _group_0_binding_N_fs. snail.shader.slang_generated records them; GL
   hosts bind both blocks to one 96-byte UBO (contract.zig PushConstants
   layout — std140 and std430 agree on every offset of this block).
8. slang/glslang strength-reduce constant divisions (c/12.92 → c*0.0774…)
   — measured pixel-exact after 8-bit quantization on all gates, but keep
   the exact-0 GL gate to catch regressions.

Stage-B traps (discovered porting colr/path; apply to later families)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
9.  Per-target bit-parity pins each leg to its own history. slangc
    strength-reduces constant divisions (srgbDecode's c/12.92 and
    (c+0.055)/1.055 become reciprocal multiplies) in BOTH its direct
    SPIR-V backend and the via-glsl leg at the default -O. The Vulkan and
    WGSL baselines came from the slangc GLSL-ingestion pipeline (same
    reduction) — keep default -O there. The GL baseline is the raw-GLSL
    catalog compiled by the driver (division preserved) — compile GL legs
    of new families with -O0 (`gl_o0` in build/slang_shaders.zig). The
    fragment-only families therefore pair with the -O0 `painted` GL
    vertex, while Vulkan/WGSL keep sharing the text vertex.
10. -O0 keeps functions un-inlined, so the dead layer component of an
    arrayed GetDimensions query survives and naga's SPIR-V front end
    rejects it ("Index 2 is out of bounds"): run
    `spirv-opt --eliminate-dead-code-aggressive` between slangc and naga
    on -O0 via-glsl legs.
11. Textually/semantically identical GLSL can still render differently:
    Mesa's multiply-add fusion is code-shape sensitive. naga's
    statement-per-op emission of the cubic Newton/bisection solver
    compiles to different fusion than the composed single-expression
    form — a 20M-input strict-IEEE CPU sweep of both transcriptions is
    bit-identical, yet llvmpipe flips scattered LSBs on cubic path edges.
    Fix: build/glsl_patch_cubic_solver.zig substitutes the composed spec
    text of `solveMonotonicCubicRoot` into the generated GL artifacts
    (`patch_cubic_solver` per family). If another family's GL gate shows
    scattered 1-LSB diffs, suspect this class first and bisect by
    splicing composed functions into the artifact.
12. Vulkan image-paint sampling: `Texture2DArray` + `SamplerState`
    aliased on one binding (set 0, binding 3) both bind from the existing
    COMBINED_IMAGE_SAMPLER descriptor — spec-legal; silence slangc's
    E39001 overlap warning. WGSL puts the sampler at @group(1)
    @binding(3) (the catalog's split-sampler slot); the GL leg fuses the
    pair back into one combined sampler (`_group_0_binding_4_fs`).
13. A via-glsl VERTEX stage (autohint: fitter loops force it) cannot use
    the spirv_asm raw-VertexIndex workaround, and SV_VertexID through
    that leg still carries D3D semantics: the naga GL output reads
    gl_BaseVertex (GL 4.6-only, absent in GLES).
    build/glsl_patch_base_vertex.zig pins the read to 0 (exact for
    snail's base-vertex-0 draws). Its uniform block also gets the
    glslang-style name (`block_SnailPushConstants_0_block_0Vertex`) —
    GL hosts try both vertex block names.
14. Command-line -D defines DO reach imported modules (verified: the
    SNAIL_TARGET_WGSL branch of snailAhFinite selects per target inside
    autohint_warp.slang — OpIsNan in the Vulkan SPIR-V, none in WGSL).
    Stage-specific variants use generics instead
    (snailFitAutohintAxis<N, IS_VERTEX>) — no cross-module preprocessor
    state needed.
15. Dual source: native [[vk::location(0)]] [[vk::index(1)]] emits the
    SPIR-V Index decoration on EVERY leg incl. via-glsl. naga still needs
    an explicit `Index 0` on the color output
    (build/spv_patch_dual_source.zig, "fragmentMain_color 0") and then
    emits `layout(location = 0, index = N)` — no
    glBindFragDataLocationIndexed needed for the native GL program. The
    WGSL backend DROPS the index (no @blend_src): the subpixel family
    generated no WGSL artifact (wgpu keeps the old catalog). [Since the
    interop spike below, a WGSL artifact IS generated via a raw-prelude
    entry — declaration-level support is still absent.]
16. A family file cannot share its BASENAME with a module it imports
    (`import text_subpixel` from families/text_subpixel.slang resolves to
    itself → "recursive module import"). Name family translation units
    distinctly (module text_subpixel_family / subpixel_body).
17. naga's SPIR-V front end rejects texel buffers (SampledBuffer /
    "unsupported image dimension"), so a Buffer<uint>-based family has no
    naga GL leg (text_sample: canonical artifacts are spirv+wgsl only;
    the GL consumer keeps composing the GLSL catalog until stage C).

