DirectX stage (2026-07-21): HLSL artifacts + minimal_d3d11 under Wine
=====================================================================
Fifth target: `hlsl` — D3D11 / SM 5.0, FXC-class. gen-shaders compiles
every non-gl_only family with
  slangc -DSNAIL_TARGET_D3D11 -target hlsl -profile sm_5_0
         -line-directive-mode none
into src/snail/shader/generated/hlsl/ (nine artifacts; linear_resolve and
game_material are gl_only by design — D3D11 renders to an sRGB RTV and has
no resolve pass). Exposed via snail.shader.generated (textHlsl/
autohintHlsl/{colr,path,ttHinted,subpixel,textSample}FragHlsl + name/
semantic constants), with artifact tests.

Findings (all verified empirically):
 - Matrix layout: the native-Slang finding CARRIES OVER — the default is
   correct, no flag. The HLSL backend emits `#pragma
   pack_matrix(column_major)` + `mul(mvp, v)`: with column-major packing
   HLSL's logical row i gathers component i of each register, so the CPU's
   column-major GLSL bytes read with GLSL `M * v` semantics. Confirmed by
   the render gate (see below); D3D's "row_major default" folklore refers
   to the fxc /Zpr flag, not what slang emits.
 - Push-constant block lands as plain `cbuffer pc_0 : register(b0)` (fxc-
   compatible; no ConstantBuffer<> syntax) with the exact 96-byte layout.
 - Registers are assigned in declaration order and land on the Vulkan
   binding numbers: t0 curve, t1 band, t2 layer-info (t2 = records buffer
   for text_sample), t3 image array, s0 image sampler — even when earlier
   textures are stripped as unused (autohint.vert keeps t2). -fvk-* flags
   do not apply to -target hlsl.
 - IO semantics: entry-point IO needs HLSL semantics or dxc/fxc reject it.
   The family structs now carry `: ATTRIBn` (vertex inputs, n = the
   instance-stream location) and `: TEXCOORDn` (varyings) next to the
   [[vk::location(n)]]s. This is a NO-OP for every other target — all
   spirv/wgsl/glsl330/gles300 artifacts stayed byte-identical.
 - SV_VertexID is simply the native semantic on this target (and spirv_asm
   is a hard error: "unexpected IR opcode during code emit"), so D3D11
   shares the WGSL entry branch — including the clip-space y-flip: D3D11
   clip space is y-up like WebGPU's, mvp = ortho(0, w, 0, h).
 - Dual source: [[vk::index(1)]] emits SV_Target0/SV_Target1 (D3D11's
   dual-source form, SRC1_* blend factors) — text_subpixel gets a
   full-fidelity HLSL artifact, no family skipped on any count.

Wine traps (Wine's d3dcompiler_47 is vkd3d-shader, not Microsoft FXC):
 - isnan/isinf are not implemented (E5005). snailAhFinite's magnitude
   test (`abs(v) <= 3.402823e38`, previously the WGSL branch) now covers
   WGSL + D3D11; Vulkan/GL keep isnan — their artifacts are unchanged.
 - Dynamic vector-component STORES are not implemented (E5017 in vkd3d
   1.19; Wine 11.0's bundled copy crashes with a page fault instead of
   erroring). snailAhPackAxis's packing loop
   (`packedTargets[i>>2][i&3] = ...`, `packedSources[word] = ...`) gets a
   SNAIL_TARGET_D3D11 [ForceUnroll] variant (break → `if (i < count)`
   guard) so every subscript is a compile-time constant.
 - Even with both fixed, stable wine 11.0 crashes in its HLSL front end on
   autohint.vert; wine 11.6 (wine64Packages.unstable in shell.nix)
   compiles all nine. Real Windows d3dcompiler_47 has none of these
   limits, but Wine is the CI environment, so the artifacts stay inside
   the vkd3d-supported subset.

Validation (cheapest that genuinely validates, per artifact class):
 1. dxc (nix directx-shader-compiler) accepts -T vs_5_0/ps_5_0 and
    compiles all nine — language/semantic validation at artifact time.
 2. vkd3d-compiler 1.19 (nix vkd3d) `-p {vs,ps}_5_0 -b dxbc-tpf` produces
    real SM5 DXBC for all nine — bytecode-level validation.
 3. The demo runtime-compiles all nine through Wine's d3dcompiler_47: the
    seven it draws with, plus text_subpixel/text_sample as compile-only
    checks (validateRemainingArtifacts) since the scene has no subpixel or
    material pass.

minimal_d3d11 (src/demo/app/minimal_d3d11.zig): mirrors minimal_wgpu's
structure and scene exactly (same fonts/atlas planner/emit stream/mvp).
Headless D3D11CreateDevice (hardware, WARP fallback), RGBA8_UNORM_SRGB
render-target texture, UpdateSubresource per planner region, the 92-byte
instance layout as 9 per-instance input-layout elements (ATTRIB0..8, one
input layout per vertex shader), premultiplied-over blend / cull-none /
