Cross-compile: zig's bundled mingw provides d3d11.h/d3dcompiler.h and the
d3d11/dxgi/d3dcompiler_47 import libs; the one external dependency is
HarfBuzz, compiled into the Windows snail module from the upstream
single-file amalgam (src/harfbuzz.cc) out of the nix-pinned source
(shell.nix exports HARFBUZZ_SRC; same pin as the host harfbuzz, so shaping
matches). `zig build run-minimal-d3d11` runs the exe under `wine` with a
hermetic WINEPREFIX=zig-out/wineprefix, WINEDEBUG=-all (first run pays
one-time prefix setup; the syswow64 warnings from the 64-bit-only wine are
harmless).

Gate (vs zig-out/minimal-gl.tga, magick compare):
  minimal-d3d11: AE @-fuzz 4% = 650/403200, raw AE = 875
  minimal-wgpu:  AE @-fuzz 4% = 650/403200, raw AE = 878   (same class)
  d3d11 vs wgpu directly: raw AE = 3, @-fuzz 4% = 0 — pixel-equivalent to
